	Introduction to DynamoDB

DynamoDB 101

Read the FAQ on this Topic

What is DynamoDB?
- Amazon DynamoDB is a fast and flexible NoSQL database service for all applications that need consistent, single-digit millisecond latency at any scale.
- It is a fully managed database and supports both document and key-value data models
- It's flexible data model and reliable performance make it a great fit for mobile, web, gaming, ad-tech, IoT and many other applications

Quick facts about DynamoDB
- Stored on SSD storage
- Spread Across 3 geographically distinct data centers

- Eventual consistent Reads(Default)
	- Consistency across all copies of data is usually reached within a second
	- Repeating a read after a short time should return the updata data (Best Read Performance)

- Strongly Consistent Reads
	- A strongly consistent read returns a result that reflects all writes that received a successful response prior to the readj